headline: Moody's Improves CABEI's Outlook from Stable to Positive
summary: Credit rating agency Moody's has improved the Central American Bank for Economic Integration's (CABEI) outlook from Stable to Positive, affirming its international credit risk rating at "Aa3." This action represents the third positive credit rating action for the Bank in the past twelve months, reaffirming its position as the best credit in Latin America.
